@startuml ia_ms_process_flow
!theme plain

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #dae8fc
skinparam participantBorderColor #6c8ebf
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam noteBorderColor #d6b656
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff2cc
skinparam dividerBackgroundColor #f0f0f0
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #f9f9f9

title Intent Assurance MS (IA MS) — Runtime Assurance Sequence

participant "Kafka\n(internal event backbone)" as KAFKA
participant "Intent Assurance MS\n(IA MS)" as IAMS
database "IA MS State Store\n(assurance state + outbox)" as STORE
participant "Observability Platform" as OBS
participant "Outbox Relay\n(background worker)" as RELAY
participant "IC MS" as ICMS

== 1. Consume IntentNetworkReadyEvent ==
IAMS -> KAFKA : consume IntentNetworkReadyEvent
IAMS -> STORE : check idempotency record\n(intentId + eventId)
alt already processed duplicate
  STORE --> IAMS : duplicate — skip
  IAMS -> KAFKA : ack idempotently
else not yet processed
  STORE --> IAMS : proceed
end

== 2. Persist Service Configuration and Runtime Context ==
group Atomic DB transaction
  IAMS -> STORE : store apply resources\nfrom serviceConfiguration.orchestratorConfiguration.resources
  IAMS -> STORE : store observer scope\nfrom serviceConfiguration.observerConfiguration.resources
  IAMS -> STORE : store resolved runtime context\nbody.expression.context
  IAMS -> STORE : write idempotency record\n(intentId + eventId → STORED)
  IAMS -> STORE : set assurance state → AwaitingApply
end

note over IAMS
IntentNetworkReadyEvent alone does not prove apply success.
Active state requires apply/callback confirmation and/or runtime observations according to workflow policy.
end note

== 3. Consume IntentCallbackEvent ==
IAMS -> KAFKA : consume IntentCallbackEvent
IAMS -> STORE : check idempotency record\n(intentId + callbackEventId)
alt duplicate callback
  STORE --> IAMS : duplicate — skip
  IAMS -> KAFKA : ack idempotently
else new callback event
  STORE --> IAMS : proceed
end

== 4. Validate and Correlate ==
IAMS -> STORE : fetch IA-owned state for intentId
STORE --> IAMS : applyResources, observerScope, runtimeContext, currentAssuranceState
alt intentId not found in IA state
  IAMS -> STORE : log unresolvable callback for audit
  IAMS -> KAFKA : ack with no further processing
else intentId resolved
  IAMS -> IAMS : continue assurance evaluation
end

== 5. Map Raw sourceState.state ==
IAMS -> IAMS : map sourceState.state to lifecycleStatus\nfor example InProgress, Active, Failed, Terminated
IAMS -> IAMS : derive statusReason from callback state,\nruntime metrics, and IA mapping policy

note over IAMS
IA MS owns mapping from raw callback state values into platform assurance semantics.
ICB MS remains thin and does not interpret service meaning.
end note

== 6. Obtain Runtime Metric Facts ==
IAMS -> OBS : query observability endpoints\ninformed by observerConfiguration.resources
OBS --> IAMS : runtime metric facts\nlatency, availability, jitter, packet loss, utilisation

== 7. Evaluate Metrics Against Targets ==
IAMS -> IAMS : evaluate observed latency, availability, jitter, and packet loss
IAMS -> IAMS : compare metrics against stored body.expression.context targets
alt all targets satisfied
  IAMS -> IAMS : assurance outcome → lifecycleStatus Active
else degraded within tolerance
  IAMS -> IAMS : assurance outcome → lifecycleStatus Degraded
else violated outside tolerance
  IAMS -> IAMS : assurance outcome → lifecycleStatus Failed or Degraded\naccording to severity policy
end

note over IAMS, STORE
IntentAssuranceEvent is metrics-first.
Use lifecycleStatus, statusReason, expression.context, current.resources.metrics, and references.
Do not use separate derived evaluation blocks by default.
end note

== 8. Update IA-Owned Assurance State ==
group Atomic DB transaction
  IAMS -> STORE : update assurance state\nlifecycleStatus, statusReason, current.resources.metrics, mapping audit
  IAMS -> STORE : write idempotency record\n(callbackEventId → PROCESSED)
  IAMS -> STORE : write IntentAssuranceEvent to IA outbox
end

== 9. Outbox Relay Publishes IntentAssuranceEvent ==
RELAY -> STORE : poll PENDING outbox rows
STORE --> RELAY : IntentAssuranceEvent
RELAY -> KAFKA : publish IntentAssuranceEvent
RELAY -> STORE : mark row DELIVERED

== 10. IC MS Consumes and Projects ==
ICMS -> KAFKA : consume IntentAssuranceEvent
ICMS -> ICMS : update external Intent lifecycle projection
ICMS -> ICMS : create or update IntentReport projection

note over ICMS
IC MS does not feed back into IA MS.
IA MS has an independent internal event publication path.
end note

== Ongoing. Periodic Observation Without Callback Trigger ==
IAMS -> STORE : fetch active observer scopes
STORE --> IAMS : intentId + observerConfiguration.resources
IAMS -> OBS : query observability endpoints on schedule
OBS --> IAMS : updated metric facts
IAMS -> IAMS : re-evaluate metrics against stored targets

group Atomic DB transaction
  IAMS -> STORE : update observation metrics and assurance state
  IAMS -> STORE : write IntentAssuranceEvent to IA outbox if state changed
end

RELAY -> STORE : poll PENDING outbox rows
RELAY -> KAFKA : publish IntentAssuranceEvent if state changed
ICMS -> KAFKA : consume IntentAssuranceEvent

@enduml
